value.Title: Migration, Borders&Walls
value.Description: Brief Course Description: We will use history, ethnography, and artistic-creative approaches to develop anthropological, interdisciplinary and multi-modal perspectives on migration and its impact on communities, individual identities and kinships. Readings will be paired with film, photographs, comics, and memes. Students will develop short essays or creative exercises on selected themes that will lead to a final paper.
